ISLAMABAD, Jun 30 (APP): Ambassador of Pakistan to Kingdom of Belgium, Dr. Asad Majeed Khan has presented credentials to Philippe Leopold Louis Marie, King of Belgians, in a graceful ceremony held at the Royal Palace of Brussels.
The ambassador conveyed the greetings and best wishes of the President and the Prime Minister of Pakistan to the King of Belgians, said a news release received here on Thursday. Reaffirming the importance Pakistan attaches to its friendly relations with Belgium, the ambassador expressed his determination to work hard for building a more strong, vibrant and diverse partnership between the two countries. The King of Belgians reciprocated the warm greetings and extended best wishes for the welfare and prosperity of the people of Pakistan.
